content_vision: I love you. Our love is difficult to maintain. You are such an despiseful bitch. It's all her fault, but she keeps making it worse because I can't fix it. Then she blames me.
text:
Intro:
I never thought our love would be so tough to tame,
but now it seems like everything's a dangerous game.

Verse 1:
But we can't give up now, we've come so far,
I'll break down these walls and show you who we are.
I never thought our love would be this wild and free,
but now it's like a maze that keeps us running endlessly.
She tells me I'm the one to blame, but I can't help but feel the pain. I try to fix it all, but she just pulls me in deeper,
I love her but she's a master of manipulation and I'm just a poor keeper.
She wears a mask, hiding her true face,
but I see through the facade and I can't erase
the love I have for her, even when she puts me through hell,
can't you see, it's you that I adore and no one else.

Pre-Chorus 1:
She may push me away, but I'll always come back,
can't help but love her despite all the flack.

Chorus 1:
But through the chaos and the pain, our love remains,
and I can't help but keep holding on.
But through the chaos and the pain, our love remains,
and I can't help but keep holding on.

Verse 2:
I try to walk away, but you pull me back in,
my heart and mind in a constant battle, I can't seem to win.
But in the midst of the chaos, there's a spark of love that just won't die,
and I'll keep fighting for us, until the end of time.
But amidst all the chaos and the pain,
there's a glimmer of hope that keeps me sane.
But despite all the craziness,
we can't seem to let go,

Pre-Chorus 2:
She's a siren, luring me in with her song,
but I'm a fool for her and I can't resist for long.

Chorus 2:
But through all the ups and downs, our love remains,
and I'm holding on tight, despite all the strains.
But through all the ups and downs, our love remains,
so I'll keep holding on, despite all the strains.
Our love may be complicated and full of pain,
but in the end, it's worth all the rain.

Bridge:
We're like fire and gasoline, burning bright despite the pain,
but every time we try to mend, we just light it up again.
You're my greatest addiction, a rollercoaster
ride I never want to get off of.

Outro:
But through all the ups and downs, we'll keep fighting for our love,
never surrendering to the chaos and drama that threatens to tear us apart.

Instrumental:
Lost in the instrumental, my heart races with each beat,
memories of our love, a bittersweet retreat.

Intro:
I remember the first time I saw your face,
butterflies in my stomach, heart starting to race.
From that moment on, I knew you were the one,
but little did I know, our love would come undone.

Intro:
As I lay here, thoughts of you consume my mind,
memories of our love, now gone, are all that I find.

Verse 1:
I thought our love would never die,
but you keep pushing me away and making me cry.
But I'll keep holding on, fighting for our love,
knowing deep down that you're the one I can't get enough of.
You keep pushing me away with every fight, but I'll keep trying, my love for you too bright,
it's not your fault, our love just needs some light.
But I'll keep holding on, fighting for our love, knowing

Pre-Chorus 1:

Chorus 1:
But despite the ups and downs, I just can't quit you,
my love, you're worth the fight.
But even though our love is causing us pain,
I can't help but love you again and again.

Verse 2:
Your words cut me like knives, I try to move on,
but our love just thrives.
I know I've made mistakes, caused our love to break,
but it's not too late, we can still mend our hearts and make it right.
But as much as I try to fix it all, your
words cut me like knives and I feel so small.
I try to hold on, try to make things right,
but your stubbornness only adds fuel to the fight.
You push me away, then blame me for the burn,
but my love for you, it continues to yearn.

Pre-Chorus 2:
I know that we both have our flaws, but our love is worth fighting for,
even when it feels like we're caught in a never-ending war.

Chorus 2:
No matter how hard we try, we just can't seem to make it right,
caught in this never-ending fight, our love a constant plight.
But I'll keep holding on, knowing you're worth the pain,
because our love, it's never been in vain.

Bridge:
But despite it all, when the dust settles and the storm subsides,
our love still remains, unbreakable and true.
But no matter who's to blame,
our love still stands strong,

Outro:
But at the end of the day, it's just you and me,
fighting for our love and trying to be free.

Instrumental:
My love for you, it's never dying,
our broken hearts, they just keep multiplying.

Intro:
It all started as a love story, now I'm questioning my sanity
I can't escape the cycle, she's my delicious agony.

Verse 1:
But I can't escape her spell, it's like a twisted game
She's got me locked in, can't break free, and I'm the one to blame.
But I'll keep coming back for more, like a moth to the flame
Even though I know she'll only bring me pain
You say you love me, but it's always on your terms;
playing games, making me the one who always squirms.
But she's like a drug to me, can't resist her pull
My heart's in pieces, but I keep playing the fool

Pre-Chorus 1:
Every time I try to break free, she
pulls me back in with her seductive lies

Chorus 1:
But I can't break away,
cause she's my guilty pleasure
I know I should let you go, but every time I try,
you pull me back in like a powerful undertow.

Verse 2:
She's like a toxic addiction, I know I should quit,
but I can't resist her sweet affliction
She's like a poison to my soul,
but I can't resist her dark allure
Our love is a volatile game, with no winners in sight
I wish I could quit you, but my heart just won't fight
But I can't deny the fire between us, it's like a force I can't control,
we may be broken, but our love is whole.

Pre-Chorus 2:
She's like a storm that I can't weather,
but I can't escape this love that binds us together.

Chorus 2:
But our love is a burning flame,
consuming everything in its path
But our love is a battlefield,
we're both casualties in this war

Bridge:
In this vicious game of love, we're both to blame,
our love is a fire that can't be tamed.
Our love is a rollercoaster that we can't seem to get off of,
but maybe that's why we keep going back for more.

Outro:
Our love may be a beautiful disaster,
but I wouldn't trade it for anything else.

Instrumental:
As the guitar weeps, my heart echoes with pain
Strumming to the beat of our love in vain.

Intro:
We used to be inseparable, couldn't get enough,
But now we're falling apart, losing all our love.

Verse 1:
But every time I try to fix things, you push me away,
you're so prideful and it's driving me insane.
But every time I lay my heart on the line, you trample over it without a second thought,
playing with my feelings like it's all just a game.
I've tried to understand your side, but all you do is deflect and hide. You say I'm the one to blame, but it's your actions that bring us shame.
Despite it all, I still love you, but I don't know what else I can do.
But every time I try to mend our broken love,
you throw it back in my face with a cruel shove.

Pre-Chorus 1:
But I can't keep chasing, my heart can only take so much,
every time I reach for you, I'm just met with cold touch.

Chorus 1:
Heartbreak, it's all we know, a never-ending
cycle we can't seem to outgrow.
But it's hard to let go, when my heart still yearns for you,
I can't seem to shake this feeling, no matter what I do.

Verse 2:
But I can't keep living in regret, chasing a love that I can't get, I'm tired of being your puppet on a string,
always pulling me back with every fling.
But I'm still holding on, can't seem to let you go,
but every time I try, you just dig a deeper hole.
But I'm starting to see things more clearly,
realizing that you're not the one for me.
But now it's clear that I was just a pawn,
in your game of manipulation and con.

Pre-Chorus 2:
But I can't keep trying, when you're just too blind to see,
it's like we're speaking different languages, can't agree.

Chorus 2:
But I can't give up, can't turn my back,
even when you attack, I still see what we lack.
But even though we're drowning in this mess, I'll
hold on to the memories of when we were at our best.

Bridge:
But no matter the blame, my love for you still remains,
it's a never-ending cycle that drives me insane.
But every time we try to mend our broken hearts, we just end up tearing each other apart,
can't seem to find our way back to love's start.

Outro:
But despite it all, I'll always cherish the moments we shared,
even if they now bring me pain.

Instrumental:
As the music fades and the lights dim,
I can't help but wonder where it all went wrong.

Intro:
I used to think you were the one for me,
but now I see it was all a fantasy.

but now those memories only bring me sighs.
I gave you my heart, but you just tore it apart
now I see, your love was just a work of art.
I thought we had it all, but you had other plans,
constantly playing games, leaving me to second-guess and doubt.
I gave you everything, but you only pushed me away,
now it's clear, your love was never meant to stay.

Pre-Chorus 1:

your love was just a game, and I was unaware.

Chorus 1:

because without you, I don't know where I'll go.

I tried to fix us, but every time I would try,
you'd just push me away,

you'd just push me away

you'd just push me away, blaming me for every lie.

Pre-Chorus 2:

Outro:

Instrumental:
The melody carries me back to our sweet beginnings,
but now all I feel is pain and endless beginnings.
